caption: This place is messed for having that picture of vomit online.

This place has some incredibly lame food. Of course it is Louisville Kentucky so you need to lower your standards a lot. Taste like peanut butter and noodles and they are calling it Indonesian. It’s one of those places you try once then make a promise to yourself to never step foot back in.

I liked it! A bit pricey for some items, but spot on for others. I had the fish special which was an interesting salmon dish. $28 and worth it! My husband had the burger $17. Not a good choice. We had the appetizer skewers $13 which were delicious and the chocolate tahini cake $11 which really surprised us flavor wise. We did not leave feeling overly full which is good since we were there for the show.  I highly recommend it for one more reason. Location. It makes getting to the theatre so much easier!!!
Horribly managed. Waiting at the host stand for what seemed like forever until a lady came up and told us to sit anywhere. THERE WAS NO SIGN STATING THIS. A SIGN WOULD BE HELPFUL.

I went here once before last year and had this amazing, expert level Japanese noodle dish. It wasn’t on the menu this time when I went to see Hamilton but I had something just as amazing.  I had the house made bologna sandwich. 🥪 First of all, I can’t believe these people are making their own bologna. Second of all I can’t believe how absolutely delicious it was.  I’m already looking forward to coming back next year. Everything I’ve tried here has been exceptional. If you’re going to a show at The Kentucky Center you should really try out their restaurant. It’s really one of my favorite places to eat when I have the opportunity.  Job well done, Scene!
I love going here. It’s not really suited for adults but I love this place. If they could update it a bit for the older crowd that would be awesome.

Food was absolutely amazing. Hands down best restaurant I have been to in Louisville. Perfect setting for a dinner before a show at the always exceptional Kentucky Center for the Arts.  Love it so very much. Keep up the great work and keep raising the bar!
What is the point of having a restaurant that doesn't have a phone number or post hours of operation?
